HEADWORD: Hemibranchi
<hw>Hem`i*bran"chi</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Hemi-</er>, and <er>Branchia</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An order of fishes having an incomplete or reduced branchial
apparatus. It includes the sticklebacks, the flutemouths, and
Fistularia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

